# Shared Memory Monitor — standalone plugin configuration
# Copy to .env. See README "Prerequisites" / AGENTS.md Part 1 before editing.
#
# This file is for the *monitor* only: COORDINATOR_URL + monitor:read token +
# optional log/backup paths. LLM API keys (token_env / LLM_BACKENDS_JSON) belong
# on the *gateway* host — never put cloud LLM secrets here. The dashboard reads
# non-secret placement (has_credential / model) from GET /health.config only.

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Read-only monitor token — mint on the gateway host via the framework's
# shared-memory/scripts/generate_tokens.py (monitor identity + AGENT_ROLES=monitor:read).
# See README "Gateway token (issued by the framework)" and framework SECURITY.md.
AGENT_TOKEN=tok_your_monitor_read_token_here

# Hive-mind gateway URL (default port 8888). Wire contract: api_version 3.
COORDINATOR_URL=http://localhost:8888

# ── Optional (log paths) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Framework repo — discovers MEMORY_LOG_PATH, AUDIT_LOG_PATH, GATEWAY_AUDIT_LOG_PATH from <root>/.env
# SHARED_MEMORY_ROOT=/path/to/shared-memory-GitHub
# SHARED_MEMORY_ROOT=../shared-memory-GitHub

# Explicit gateway .env path (alternative to SHARED_MEMORY_ROOT for log paths)
# SM_GATEWAY_ENV=/path/to/shared-memory/.env

# Neo4j Browser nav link in dashboard
# NEO4J_BROWSER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:7474

# Known stale neo4j_outbox.id values excluded from failure alerts (baseline estimate)
# SM_IGNORED_OUTBOX_IDS=4

# User-scoped systemd unit for gateway log tab:
#   journalctl --user -u hive-mind-gateway.service
# SM_JOURNAL_UNIT=hive-mind-gateway.service

# ── Optional (backup status) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Directory where ops/backup.sh writes sm-backup-*.manifest.json on the gateway
# host. The Status sidebar reads the newest manifest's "created" field for
# "Last <date>". Live backup-in-progress still comes from GET /health
# (backup_in_progress). Default: ~/.shared-memory/backups (framework .env).
# Set explicitly when backups are stored elsewhere (external disk, NFS, etc.):
# BACKUP_DIR=/path/to/backups